entries.femaleVariant: What language is she speaking?
Try scanning the phone.
Got it.  Give it a second...
Have to know what they're saying.
We have to know what they're saying. Could be important.
Fine. Just found the auto-translate package.
OK, Judy. We're good.
Should get along fine with your system. I'll install it now.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Tipoupe a deja ale?" t="The doll has left?" b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Wi li ale. Ou te gen rezon, manzè twò entelijan pou sa pote l byen." t="Yes. You were right, she's too smart for her own good." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ou panse manzè qp fè n gen pwoblèm?" t="Will she bring us trouble?" b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Manzè pa enraje." t="She wouldn't dare." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Anplis, se pi bon mwayen nou genyen pou nou rive sou Yorinobu. Fòk nou pran chans lan." t="Besides, she's our best route to Yorinobu. We must take this risk." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Mwen ta swete mwen kwè menm jan avè, Silvèhan ap mennen nou dirèk sou Alt." t="I wish I shared your confidence that Silverhand will lead us to Alt." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ou gen yon pi bon lide?" t="You have a better idea?" b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Trèbyen, si w deside sispan kritike sa m panse, al kontinye fè travay ou." t="Good, then if you're done questioning my judgment, you can get back to work." b="" a=""/>
Dunno... Haitian Creole? It is the Voodoo Boys…
Didn't I…? Wait, lemme see if I've got an auto-translator.
Meantime, you try to tune into the phone's frequency.
See what the other side's sayin'.
Heard something about Yorinobu.
Heard her mention Yorinobu.
Probably why Evelyn buried this recording deep.
Caught another name... something like... Silverhand?
All right. Disconnecting.
[Scan]
